RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 1 6F Turf CR: 99. Claiming Purse 39000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since July 29 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $32,000, if for $28,000, allowed 1 lb. (Maiden And Claiming Races For $25,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances ). (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GIVE ME THE LUTE was prominent early then pulled the rider along when taking in hand, switch to the outside and went up to pressure the leader at the seven-sixteenths pole, dueled around the bend, put a head in front at the top of the lane, led into deep stretch and prevailed. INCH brushed with inner rival at the start, stalked two wide into the turn, tipped out in the lane and took aim at the leaders, finished gamely from outside but could not get by. SUBSIDIZE lacked early speed, saved ground through the turn, tipped off the inside, put in a late bid between foes and missed the place. WESTWARD LOOK sped clear to take control early, pressured leaving the backstretch, dueled from inside through the turn, lost command at the top of the lane, fought back into deep stretch and was outfinished. JAMMING EDDY was bothered by MAVEN coming out over the dirt crossing and had to take up, raced between rivals into and around the turn in the two path and could not rally. MARGOT'S BOY brushed leaving the gate, traveled three deep near the back to the stretch and failed to respond. MAVEN hustled from the gate then jumped crossing onto the dirt then again moving back onto the turf, chased from inside to the lane and weakened.

ENTRY.NAME: Maven
ENTRY.OWNER: Hanson Ryan Kayajanian Jack and Mouradick Thomas
ENTRY.COMMENT: hustled, jumped xing, chased inside, weakened

ENTRY.NAME: Subsidize
ENTRY.COMMENT: lacked early speed, saved ground, tipped out, late bid between

ENTRY.NAME: Inch
ENTRY.COMMENT: brushed start, stalked off rail, 2wide, tipped out, gamely

ENTRY.NAME: Give Me the Lute
ENTRY.OWNER: Davis Racing LLC Giordano Louis A and Mueller Martin

ENTRY.NAME: Westward Look
ENTRY.OWNER: Altamira Racing Stable and Newman Roger H

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 2 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 94. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 63000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $18,000 ONCE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR STATE BRED OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $50,000. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Other Than Maiden, Claiming Or Starter Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $50,000 (Non-Starters For A Claiming Price Of $25,000 Or Less In Their Last 3 Starts Preferred)(Horses Entered For The Allowance Are Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: POETICA rated behind the front-runners, waited along the inside on the turn, roused at the quarter pole and snuck through leaving the bend, took over at the top of the stretch, cleared with a furlong remaining under mild urging and was lightly coaxed to the wire. ESSENTIAL BUSINESS set the pace inside SHE'S RESILIENT, showed the way two wide through the turn, leaving too much room for POETICA to challenge from inside past the quarter pole, lost command at the three-sixteenths pole and stayed on for a clear second. KRISTI'S TIGER trailed into and around the bend in the two path, showed a mild response when called upon and got up for the show. AMERICAN LILY steadied early, stalked three wide into the turn, challenged three to four wide with a quarter mile remaining but flattened out in the furlong grounds. SHE'S RESILIENT pressed the pace from outside, could not stay with the leaders late on the turn and weakened in the lane.

ENTRY.NAME: Poetica
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated, snuck thru inside, mild urging

ENTRY.NAME: Essential Business
ENTRY.OWNER: Cady Todd Leatherman Ty and Rothblum Steve

ENTRY.NAME: Kristi's Tiger
ENTRY.OWNER: Mia Familia Racing Stable and Rockingham Ranch

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 3 6F Turf CR: 87. Maiden Special Weight Purse 61000. FOR CALIFORNIA BRED OR CALIFORNIA SIRED MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. (Non-Starters For A Claiming Price Of $40,000 Or Less In Their Last Starts Preferred). (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GRAZED chased from outside then took a brief hold to move down inside, waited behind the leaders along the rail around the bend, tipped two wide leaving the turn, angled out in upper stretch and drove clear. MAN O ROSE antsy in the gate, pressed three deep up the backstretch, vied for command around the bend and took over late on the turn, overtaken by GRAZED approaching the sixteenth pole and managed to save the place. ANTIBES trailed on the inside into the turn, lacked room at the five-sixteenths pole, tipped two wide late on the bend, moved out further in the drive, rallied and missed second. TOPPERS WAGER settled inside, moved out in the lane and improved position. GRAND TIGER set the pace under pressure from outer rivals, vied around the bend and lost command past the quarter pole, then weakened in the stretch run. TOUCHDOWN KITTLE broke inward, pressed the pace from between runners, fought through the turn and also weakened in the lane. BEYOND COMPARE broke in, prominent early then got bothered by inner rival before the half-mile pole and lost ground, dropped back two then three wide on the turn and faded.

ENTRY.NAME: Man O Rose
ENTRY.OWNER: B and B Zietz Stables, Inc.

ENTRY.NAME: Antibes
ENTRY.COMMENT: inside, lacked room 5/16, angled out, missed 2nd

ENTRY.NAME: Grazed
ENTRY.OWNER: Shanderella Stables and Anderson Robert W
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated inside-2wide, angled out, drove clear

WINNERS_DETAILS.BREEDER: Mike Weeks, Lynda Weeks & Devyn Weeks

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 4 1M Dirt CR: 76. Claiming Purse 24000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SWEET HELLO broke a step slow then rushed up to the front and led four wide into the clubhouse turn, cleared and crossed over to the two path around the bend, showed the way along the rail into the drive, kicked clear in upper stretch, ridden along into deep stretch and coasted in approaching the wire. MISS KALINE brushed the winner leaving the gate, stalked two to three wide outside a rival, got bumped entering the backstretch, was closest in pursuit entering the lane, was no match for the winner in upper stretch and churned on to secure the place. LIKE NO OTHER bobbled at the start but still came away on top, rated along the inside, drifted out and bumped rival entering the backstretch, lost ground chasing after the winner on the far turn, asked right handed into the stretch and weakened. POINT AND SHOOT chased four then three wide on the first turn, remained off the rail to the stretch and failed to menace. ASPIRATIONAL stalked from inside, dropped back in the middle stages, continued along the rail through the far turn and was not a factor.

ENTRY.COMMENT: brushed start, stalked 2-3wide, bumped 11/16, no match

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 5 6F Turf CR: 77. Maiden Special Weight Purse 61000. FOR CALIFORNIA BRED OR CALIFORNIA SIRED MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. (Non-Starters For A Claiming Price Of $40,000 Or Less In Their Last Starts Preferred). (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: POTITO vied with outer rivals then assumed command up the backstretch, maintained command through the turn, fought with IMMELMANN down the lane and held gamely to the wire. IMMELMANN took a bump from outside at the start, forwardly placed four then three deep, challenged from outside, fought with POTITO through the lane and could not get by. NESTUCKA tracked between rivals, three deep at the quarter pole, spun four wide into the lane and finished well for a game third. HIGH KING was off slow from inside, chased from off the pace, traveled along the rail through the turn before tipping two wide entering the lane, looked to make a run but got boxed in through the final furlong and kept on without ever gaining clear path. ANNAN broke in and bumped rival, tugged up the backstretch, eventually running into a tight spot and put on the brakes entering the turn, tipped two then three wide around the bend, rallied while brushing with HIGH KING and needed to find more late. WHISKEY RYE raced up close three deep then applied some pressure from between rivals around the bend, got put in a bit tight entering the lane, lacked room in the stretch and weakened late. LAST CALL PAUL showed some early speed then chased up the backstretch, saved ground through the turn and lacked a bid. DON'T HIT ME BASH settled outside a pair of rivals, traveled four deep at the quarter pole, got floated out into the lane and lacked a rally. FLEET BROTATO was off a bit slow and dropped back under coaxing, passed a rival on the turn, came three wide into the drive and failed to menace. BILLY JOE SHAVER broke a step slow, raced greenly with some awkward steps up the backstretch, eased around the turn and down the lane and walked off.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 6 6F Dirt CR: 72. Maiden Claiming Purse 35000. FOR CALIFORNIA BRED OR CALIFORNIA SIRED MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $50,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SHES JUST FLUFFY away quickly then rated outside the top pair, bid three then two wide around the bend, took over in upper stretch and drove clear in the deep stretch. ROSIE ANN RULES hit the gate and bumped between rivals, altered in early and moved into stalking position up the backstretch, tipped two wide to go around weakening rival on the turn, moved back inside once clear, steered out in the lane and got up for second. ELTONSINGSANOTHER got bumped from inner rival, drifted in some and brushed same foe and rider had to grab hold briefly, pressed from outside, dueled for command from outside, put away inner rival past the three-eighths pole but had already been challenged by SHES JUST FLUFFY to the outside, relinquished the lead to the rival in upper stretch, stayed on through the final furlong but got nailed for second. TURQUOISE BIKINI chased two wide into the turn, spun three wide into the lane and weakened. JUST IS broke a bit slow and brushed with inner rival, chased four wide into the turn, made some progress while moving into the three path around the bend but flattened out in the lane. SAHARA SUE stumbled sharply leaving the gate, trailed four wide into and around the bend and failed to make an impact. NO CAN QUIT broke alertly then drifted out and bumped rival early, set the pace under pressure from outer rival, dueled then failed to keep up past the three-eighths pole, started to weaken around the bend and retreated.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 7 1M Turf CR: 93. Claiming Purse 34000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $32,000. (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: AURELIAN MAN stalked the pace from inside, angled out at the five-sixteenths pole to take aim three wide leaving the bend, drew alongside THIRTY FOUR COUPE and battled down the stretch, dug in late and edged away from the runner-up. THIRTY FOUR COUPE pressed the pace from outside, gained the advantage late on the far turn, put away inner rival then fought with AURELIAN MAN through the lane and yielded grudgingly late. NUMERO DIX (GB) settled in the three path, rounded the far turn two wide, moved out in stretch and gained the show. BROTHER REID traveled two wide at the back early, remained in that path on the far turn, kept on through the drive and rounded out the superfecta. WORKDAY took control from inside, set the pace under pressure, was overtaken late on the far turn and weakened in the lane. BEAR MOUNTAIN stalked the top pair from outside in the three path, got floated out to the four path at the five-sixteenths pole and faded in the stretch run. ROAD OF LOVE tracked four deep into the clubhouse turn, ridden along three to four wide on the second bend and lacked a rally. DEVELOPING THE WAY moved to the inside racing near the back, ridden along on the far turn and failed to make an impact. THEMAINPROTAGONIST (IRE) broke a step slow and was coaxed along but then started to pull shortly after, chased in the two path around the clubhouse turn out of range, moved inside on the second bend and weakened.

ENTRY.NAME: Themainprotagonist (IRE)
ENTRY.OWNER: Benowitz Family Trust CYBT McLean Racing Stables Gevertz Saul and Nentwig Michae

ENTRY.NAME: Aurelian Man
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked inside, angled 3wide, dug in late

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Chillingworth S. - Grade3 SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 8 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 101. Stakes Purse 100000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE-YEAR-OLDS AND UPWARD. By subscription of $100 each if made on or before Friday, September 15, 2023, closed with 14 or by Supplementary nomination of $2,000 due at time of entry. $750 to enter and an additional $750 to start wit h $100,000 guaranteed of which 60,000 to the winner, 20,000 to second, 12,000 to third, 6,000 to fourth and 2,000 to fifth. Three-Year-Olds 122 lbs. Older 126 lbs. Non-Winners of a Graded Stakes allowed 2 lbs. Non-Winners of Sweepstakes allowed 4 lbs. At rophy will be presented to the winning owner.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: KIRSTENBOSCH was off slow to begin, chased from off the pace up the backstretch, made progress along the rail then angled out leaving the bend, closed in rapidly from outside, reeled in the leader past the sixteenth pole and drove clear. CLEARLY UNHINGED vied for the lead from inside, inched ahead on the turn, shook free at the top of the lane, remained clear to midstretch but could not offer any resistance to the winner in the final sixteenth. EDA pressed the pace four deep up the backstretch, chased the leaders four to three wide around the bend, raced within striking distance in the final furlong but could not summon the needed late kick. ELM DRIVE vied three deep up the backstretch and around the turn, fought outside the leader leaving the bend, could not go on with CLEARLY UNHINGED in upper stretch and weakened in the furlong grounds. VIOLENT RUNNER raced up close five deep to the turn, angled down to the three path around the bend, got floated out into the drive and weakened. LADY T trailed five wide into and around the bend and could not make an impact. HOME COOKING challenged for command between foes to the quarter pole and faded in the stretch run.

ENTRY.NAME: Clearly Unhinged
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied inside, shook free, yielded late

ENTRY.NAME: Home Cooking
ENTRY.OWNER: Pegram Michael E Watson Karl and Weitman Paul

ENTRY.NAME: Kirstenbosch
ENTRY.COMMENT: off slow, gained inside, angled out, reeled in foe

ENTRY.NAME: Violent Runner
ENTRY.COMMENT: up close 5deep, 5-3wide, floated into str, weakened

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 9 1M Turf CR: 92. Maiden Claiming Purse 38000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $62,500, if for $50,000, allowed 2 lbs. (Non-Starters For A Claiming Price Of $25,000 Or Less In Their Last Start Preferred). (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BELMONT BILL showed speed between rivals then ceded command on the clubhouse turn, stalked the leading pair along the inside into the far turn, lacked room into the stretch, tipped out into the clear, reached the front midstretch and kicked clear under hand urging. CAPTAIN CHOOCHIES bumped in the beginning, pressed the pace from outside, drifted inward while battling with inner rival in upper stretch, could not match BELMONT BILL in deep stretch and stayed on to save second. CRYPTO MAN tracked the pace from inside, found traffic behind rivals, altered out in upper stretch, finished well and missed the place. QUINTECENTS away quickly to take the front, set the pace under pressure, maintained a short lead over CAPTAIN CHOOCHIES through the far turn and into the lane, resisted into the final furlong, relinquished the lead midstretch and weakened. NO SECRET settled a bit off the rail then moved inside, cut the corner into the lane and improved position. TOKAMAK broke out and bumped rival, checked into the first turn, raced outside a rival then between in the middle stages, rounded the far turn three then two wide, ran into traffic briefly at the three-sixteenths pole and could not threaten. AUTOLINE (IRE) got bumped on both sides at the start, chased four wide into the clubhouse turn, steered out briefly then moved back in a few paths to race three wide, got crowded between rivals into the far turn, rounded the far turn three wide and lacked a rally. SIX MAGPIES (IRE) reserved early on then began to pull and had to steered out from behind rivals on the clubhouse turn, was on the move four then three wide on the second bend but flattened out in the stretch run. CHURCHMEISTER unhurried in the beginning and tucked inside, was a bit rank on the backstretch, continued along the rail into the far turn, encountered some mild traffic in the lane and could not rally. CHIEFS BLANKET chased three then two wide on the clubhouse turn, lost positions still in the two path on the second bend, moved out in the drive and weakened. BOLTS DESTINY broke a step slow, raced four wide into the clubhouse turn, traveled outside a rival or two wide on the second bend and was not a factor.

ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked inside, traffic, altered upper, missed 2nd

ENTRY.OWNER: Guernsey Jade H and Osborne Candice J
ENTRY.COMMENT: ceded, stalked duo, lacked room 3/16, hand urging
